  <h2>Pager</h2>
  <p>Quick previous and next links for simple pagination implementations with light markup and styles. It's great for simple sites like blogs or magazines.</p>

  <h3>Default example</h3>
  <p>By default, the pager centers links.</p>
  <div class="bs-docs-example">
    <ul class="pager">
      <li><a href="#">Previous</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Next</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
<div class="tab-content">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade in active" id="pager-haml">
%ul.pager
  %li
    %a{:href => "#"} Previous
  %li
    %a{:href => "#"} Next
</pre>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade" id="pager-html">
&lt;ul class="pager"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Previous&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#"&gt;Next&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</pre>
</div>
<ul class="nav nav-pills example-types">
  <li class="active"><a href="#pager-haml" data-toggle="tab">HAML</a></li>
  <li><a href="#pager-html" data-toggle="tab">HTML</a></li>
</ul>

  <h3>Aligned links</h3>
  <p>Alternatively, you can align each link to the sides:</p>
  <div class="bs-docs-example">
    <ul class="pager">
      <li class="previous"><a href="#">&larr; Older</a></li>
      <li class="next"><a href="#">Newer &rarr;</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
<div class="tab-content">
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade in active" id="pager-aligned-haml">
%ul.pager
  %li.previous
    %a{:href => "#"} &larr; Older
  %li.next
    %a{:href => "#"} Newer &rarr;
</pre>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums tab-pane fade" id="pager-aligned-html">
&lt;ul class="pager"&gt;
&lt;li class="previous"&gt;
&lt;a href="#"&gt;&amp;larr; Older&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class="next"&gt;
&lt;a href="#"&gt;Newer &amp;rarr;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</pre>
</div>
<ul class="nav nav-pills example-types">
  <li class="active"><a href="#pager-aligned-haml" data-toggle="tab">HAML</a></li>
  <li><a href="#pager-aligned-html" data-toggle="tab">HTML</a></li>
</ul>

